&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years post-qualification experience, with considerable in-house experience in a fast-growth environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corporate and commercial law background, with experience across SaaS, employment law, data privacy, technology and IP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current Australian practising certificate (unrestricted)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;LLB, Juris Doctor or equivalent qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting corporate transactions, including fundraising, secondary sales, M&amp;amp;A and multi-jurisdictional employee equity plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of using AI and automation to cut legal cycle times, from contract automation and DoA automation through to faster drafting and review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced drafting and negotiation skills across a broad range of commercial agreements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong commercial acumen and the ability to balance risk against pragmatic, business-first outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing an in-house team and coordinating external counsel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice-to-haves&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of the healthcare sector and its regulatory environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
